cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with neural sequence-to-sequence models and their performance on a morphological task. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes new methods for addressing the problem of small training sets, which involves machine learning techniques such as transductive learning and source selection. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper may also belong to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as it deals with the problem of generating missing forms in a paradigm, which involves manipulating and organizing data structures.
